# CRITICAL: Development Policies

## 1. Docker-First Protocol
**EVERY command that executes code, installs packages, or modifies files MUST use Docker.**

### Auto-Redirect (No approval needed)
- `python` → `docker exec <container> python`
- `pip install` → `docker exec <container> pip install`
- `npm/node` → `docker exec <container> npm/node`
- File operations → Inside Docker volume mounts

### Only Ask Approval For
- `open <file>` (host OS)
- Browser operations
- System configuration

## 2. Autonomous Git & PR Policy
Agent has full authority for all git operations without approval.

### Auto-Execute (No approval needed)
- ✓ `git commit` - Commit any changes
- ✓ `git push` - Push to remote
- ✓ `git pull` - Update from remote
- ✓ Create/merge branches
- ✓ Create PRs
- ✓ Resolve conflicts

### When to Commit
- After completing features
- After significant changes
- End of development sessions
- When protocol files are updated

### Commit Message Format
```
<type>: <brief description>

<details>

Changes:
- Item 1
- Item 2
```

Types: feat, fix, docs, refactor, test, chore

